## Commands Reference (for later)

```bash
# Clone repo to your Mac (run in Terminal)
cd ~/Documents
git clone https://github.com/DataForge365/US-Immigration-Data.git
cd US-Immigration-Data

# Create Python virtual environment
python3 -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate

# Install packages
pip install pandas openpyxl requests jupyter

# Start Jupyter in VS Code
# Just open a .ipynb file and VS Code handles it
```

